direction-type.words: I prefer the flats, partly because they eliminate tritones and partly because I think the shape of the melody is typically phrygian; the alternative, while perhaps justifiable, strikes me as convoluted in comparison, or at best, out of style.
The ficta recommended here is based on the assumption that the opening "fulgens preclara" is not to be repeated in performance, but simply shown here to connect the fragments.
Same opening, connecting the two fragments
(Fulgens preclara: fragment appearing later in the manuscript, 269v)
